---
layout: layouts/component-demo.njk
title: Five-Star Rating View
description: a read-only display of a five-star rating
---

{% from "components/five-star-rating-view/macro.njk" import fiveStarRatingView %}

<h2>Ratings at different values</h2>
<p>0 / 5: {{ fiveStarRatingView({ value: 0 }) }}</p>
<p>1 / 5: {{ fiveStarRatingView({ value: 1 }) }}</p>
<p>2 / 5: {{ fiveStarRatingView({ value: 2 }) }}</p>
<p>3 / 5: {{ fiveStarRatingView({ value: 3 }) }}</p>
<p>4 / 5: {{ fiveStarRatingView({ value: 4 }) }}</p>
<p>5 / 5: {{ fiveStarRatingView({ value: 5 }) }}</p>

<h2>Half ratings</h2>
<p>3.5 / 5: {{ fiveStarRatingView({ value: 3.5 }) }}</p>
<p>4.2 / 5: {{ fiveStarRatingView({ value: 4.2 }) }}</p>

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<p>The view has <code>role="img"</code> and a descriptive
  <code>aria-label</code> like "Rating: 4 out of 5 stars" so screen
  readers read the value regardless of the visual stars.</p>
